-- Algeria Shuts Down Border With Mali, State-Run APS Reports
-- B y   S a l a h   S l i m a n i
-- 2013-01-14T20:53:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-14/algeria-shuts-down-border-with-mali-state-run-aps-reports.html
Algeria  closed its border with  Mali 
and has informed the Mali government of its decision, state run
APS news agency reported today, citing Amar Belani, spokesman
for Algeria’s Foreign Ministry  The decision came at the end of a two day visit to Algeria
by Mali’s Prime Minister Diango Cissoko.  Discussions on the situation in the region allowed both
sides to reach a convergence of views on issues related to the
crisis in Mali, the news service cited Belani as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salah Slimani in Algiers at 
 sslimani2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
